item.description:
arXiv:2504.15968v1 Announce Type: cross 
Abstract: This paper investigates the profile decomposition of Palais-Smale sequences associated with a Br\'ezis-Nirenberg-type problem involving a combination of local nonlocal operator, given by
  \begin{equation*}
  \begin{aligned}
  &-\Delta u + (-\Delta)^s u - \lambda u = |u|^{2^*-2}u \;\;\mbox{ in } \Omega,
  &\quad u=0\,\mbox{ in }\mathbb{R}^N\setminus \Omega.
  \end{aligned}
  \end{equation*} where $ N \geq 3$ and $2^* = \frac{2N}{N - 2} $ denotes the critical Sobolev exponent. As an application of the derived global compactness result, we further study the corresponding Coron-type problem.
